        </div>
        <div id="collapseLearnMore" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <a href="http://www.crowdacting.org/">www.crowdacting.org</a>.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseStart">
            <h3 class="panel-title">
                <span class="fa fa-play-circle" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;
                CAN I START A PROJECT?
                <span class="fa fa-angle-down pull-right"></span>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseStart" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                Yes! You can create a project @Html.ActionLink("here", "Start", "Projects"). Make sure you first check here if your idea meets the criteria.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseCriteria">
            <h3 class="panel-title">
                <span class="fa fa-list" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;
                WHAT ARE THE CRITERIA THAT A PROJECT MUST MEET?
                <span class="fa fa-angle-down pull-right"></span>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseCriteria" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                A project may only be placed if it meets the following criteria:
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        The project aims to make a positive social and / or environmental contribution to your neighborhood, city, country or the world.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project is not aimed at personal gain.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project does not involve initiatives aimed at conversion or activism (religious or political).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project does not involve initiatives that are illegal and do not meet the regulatory requirements of the Netherlands or the country of export.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The online project application form is fully and truthfully filled with a bright, clear and readable project description and objectives. The CollAction team may request and / or edit your text clarification if necessary.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Project Starter has thought carefully about how people of commitment can be moved to action. Here we can help you!
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The project is ambitious but realistic - the CollAction review committee assesses whether this is the case. Project Starter can / activate its own network, and / or have a good plan to reach your target
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The Starter Project is committed to assess the impact of the measure (number of people who have taken action) and to share this information with CollAction.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseHowLong">
            <h3 class="panel-title">
                <span class="fa fa-clock-o" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;
                HOW LONG DOES AN ACTION?
                <span class="fa fa-angle-down pull-right"></span>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseHowLong" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                Some actions are disposable - think of a switch to a fair bank or green energy. Other projects may take longer. For example, eating less meat, visits periodically lonely elderly, or helping refugees with Dutch lessons. In other words, the duration of the action saves per project.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseNotReached">
            <h3 class="panel-title">
                <span class="fa fa-stop" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;
                WHAT HAPPENS IF A TARGET IS NOT REACHED?
                <span class="fa fa-angle-down pull-right"></span>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseNotReached" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                Then, in principle, no one need to come into action. Acting crowd means no cure, no action. But if you really are inspired to do take action, we welcome that, of course.
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading" data-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseHowKnow">
            <h3 class="panel-title">
                <span class="fa fa-rocket" aria-hidden="true"></span>&nbsp;
                HOW DO I KNOW THAT PEOPLE ACTUALLY TAKE ACTION?
                <span class="fa fa-angle-down pull-right"></span>
            </h3>
        </div>
        <div id="collapseHowKnow" class="panel-collapse collapse">
            <div class="panel-body">
                You know that is not always 100% sure. By acting crowd goes initially to trust. Trust that people want to work together for a better world. Confidence that people are attached to their karma points. And trust that people honor their agreements. We hope to create a community of people who take their commitment seriously and we are trying to create a culture where deal is a deal.
                <br />
                That said, we also build some processes to maximize commitments into action! What these processes are precisely, depends on the type of project. For some projects (such as switching projects, for example to a fair bank or green energy) the transition may already conditionally be put in motion at the time of commitment. If the target is reached then automatically be supporters of the project transferred. When local projects of social control will play a greater role. Still other projects are purely on trust. We will extensively experiment with different tricks, tools and approaches. We ask you to start thinking of projects carefully about this question - the team CollAction stands ready to contribute ideas!
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

